pullRequest.title: Do not allow publish interval configurability for telemetry and FSS less than default.
pullRequest.bodyText:
Issue #, if available:
Description of changes:
Only allow configurability of publish interval for FSS and telemetry if the value is higher than the default.
Remove publish topic configurability.
Why is this change necessary:
The customers should not be able to configure a lower value for publish interval than the default since telemetry is offered as a free feature.
How was this change tested:
Updated tests.
Any additional information or context required to review the change:
Checklist:

 Updated the README if applicable
 Updated or added new unit tests
 Updated or added new integration tests
 Updated or added new end-to-end tests

By submitting this pull request, I confirm that you can use, modify, copy, and redistribute this contribution, under the terms of your choice.

commit.message: Do not allow publish interval configurability for telemetry and FSS less than default. Remove publish topic configurability.
Fix accesibility for test feartures interface and methods.

nodes.bodyText: why is all this stuff public now? Keep things private or package-private.
if you're pulling the intvalue, why are you using Double? Why not just Integer?
Do we need to log here? Also if the current value is larger than DEFAULT_PERIODIC_UPDATE_INTERVAL_SEC, should we reduce it to DEFAULT_PERIODIC_UPDATE_INTERVAL_SEC?
